I mean, if you have to point to four or five different articles to support a claim of it being derivative, that just means it casts a wide net of inspiration  Like, literally any story on this site can be boiled down to its individual plot points, and no plot point has ever just been used once. I'm fine with the second half of your criticism and I think that if this article's plot points matched one other article's beat for beat, you could say it was derivative. But as it is, having 4 different similarities with 4 different articles is far from derivative. Also - all your examples linked, save Dead Men, is just another article that uses the plot structure of `Foundation fucks something up`, which is like - barely even a trope? Certainly not enough to be a criticism.





