Copying multiple plot points, beat-for-beat, from multiple different articles and stringing them together into a single work is derivative. Two major tropes this article leans on heavily  are 'Foundation fucks something up by cross-testing and repeated testing' and 'Foundation testing on D-Classes comes back to bite them'. But it fails to build on either trope in a unique or compelling way, which only exacerbates the issue of a predictable and uninspired plot. I’m particularly disappointed that the D-Class’s potential character arc simply ended with her turning into a monster and killing a lot of offscreen grunts.





